                    </div>
                    <span>Please note this negative review is NOT about the contents and authors but ONLY the print quality of the book. The standard-priced copy I ordered and received from Amazon was the worst I have seen. I honestly don't know if it is Prentice Hall PTR decision to print books in such poor quality or I received a faked copy from Amazon. 
<br />
<br />The whole book is just like a photocopy from the original book. Some of the printed words are so faint that it is hard to read; on the first page of most chapters, the first letter in the opening sentence is half-missing in the print; the paper used was obvious of inferior quality. I would actually doubt it is an original real book. I have not read the book yet. This sounds like a good book but you need to be able to read it as well. Hope others will take note before ordering any book from Prentice Hall, from which I have many other books before and they are of good print quality.
<br />
<br />
<br /></span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">I must have book on programming for Windows</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
